  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Who We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li><p>Confident, outgoing individuals who are comfortable engaging in face-to-face conversations.</p></li><li><p>Resilient and self-motivated — you view challenges and rejection as opportunities for growth.</p></li><li><p>Coachable, driven, and eager to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Conduct daily sales activities, including cold calling, scheduling client appointments, preparing presentation materials and proposals, and presenting to potential customers.</p></li><li><p>Develop and execute strategies by analyzing current market trends and needs.</p></li><li><p>Generate new leads and secure new sales opportunities to boost sales revenue and achieve sales targets.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with partners and cross-departmental teams to provide pricing details and technical support to customers.</p></li><li><p>Ensure accuracy in sales reports for record-keeping and management reporting.</p></li><li><p>Perform pre-ITQ and RFQ groundwork duties, including tender/bidding and negotiation to close deals.</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong support and relationships with existing and new customers, fostering long-term partnerships.</p></li><li><p>Stay updated on product knowledge and market trends by attending product training sessions and keeping up with the latest developments.</p></li><li><p>Other ad-hoc duties assigned</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 1-2 years of work experience in Business-to-Business sales or in Business development role (IT field will be an advantage).</p></li><li><p>Proven good sales track record in related fields.</p></li><li><p>Excellent communicator with good presentation skills.</p></li></ul><p></p>",
